Business Brief -- Nissan Motor Co.:
   UK Unit Plans to Increase
   Its Annual Production Rate
Nissan has been manufacturing its Bluebird model at
Sunderland in northern England since 1986. The Sunderland
plant has been devoted to the production of the Primera since
1991, when 124,000 units were built. Next year, the Micra
will also be produced there as well.
   Nissan said it intends to increase its UK investment by
#150 million ($265 million) this year to a total of #850
million, giving the plant an overall annual production
capacity of 300,000 units.